comments.body:
Because we don't actually know the length of the first bit (or really any other part, though ) of the string:

{code}
> times <- c("2012-05-25 18:45:32", "2020-5-6", "20-05-06", "2022-06-07 00:55", "2020-01-01 could be anything at all ROFL")
> strptime(times, format = "%Y-%m-%d")
[1] "2012-05-25 CDT" "2020-05-06 CDT" "0020-05-06 LMT" "2022-06-07 CDT"
[5] "2020-01-01 CST"
{code}

Or with {{%B}} it's even worse:
{code}
> months_plus <- c("2020 January 1 string", "2020 July 1 extra")
> strptime(months_plus, format = "%Y %B %d") 
[1] "2020-01-01 CST" "2020-07-01 CDT"
{code}
